directory: .
summary: Root of the agent-toolchain workspace. Exposes three independently deployable binaries — `ctx-access`, `ctx-check`, and `ctx-summarize` — backed by narrow library crates. This is the top-level composition point; all agent-facing contracts originate here.
children:
  - crates: Houses all three crate pairs (binary + library) that constitute the full agent toolchain.
key_invariants:
  - All agent interaction with source files, verification, and summarization flows through the binaries defined in this workspace.
  - No cross-crate dependencies within the workspace; each crate is independently deployable.